    "Similarly, the output node of the column of the addressed memristor is grounded through the sensing amplifier, which measures the current flowing out of this column (the other columns are at V DD /2).",
    "Such current is proportional to the applied voltage pulses and the memristor conductance plus the parasitic wire resistance corresponding to the addressed device (M i,j).",
    "This allows to estimate the conductance of the addressed memristor.",
    "This process is represented by the simplified equivalent circuit shown in the inset of Fig. 21.Before starting the write process, we translate the conductance matrix for each partition to a currents matrix, by multiplying each element g i,j by V READ.",
    "In this way, we obtain a measurable quantity for each of the elements in the conductance matrix."
